---
description: Change discipline and refactor control
globs: ["**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Change scope must remain controlled.

Rules:
- do not opportunistically refactor unrelated modules
- do not reformat unrelated files
- do not upgrade dependencies casually
- do not move files unless the task truly requires it
- if a requested feature reveals a deeper architecture problem, explain it before large refactors
- prefer incremental change sets over sweeping rewrites

Allowed refactors:
- small local extraction to improve clarity
- shared helper extraction when duplication is direct and current
- boundary-preserving cleanup around touched code

Not allowed by default:
- broad naming rewrites
- folder reorganizations
- replacing existing patterns repo-wide